Interface IMergeItem

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnnotationMenu, CheckMergeItem, ConstraintsMenu, DotsMenu, DrawingEditMenu, DrawingFileMenu, DrawingFormatMenu, DrawingViewMenu, FileMenu, FileMenu, HelpMenu, ImageDialog.PrintMenu, IMergeItem.Proxy, MainMenu, MainMenu, MergeButton, MergeButton.Separator, MergeItem, MergeItem.Separator, MergeMenu, MergeToggleButton, NucleicAcidMenu, OligoWalkWindow.OligoWalkResultsMenu, PlotMenu, PredictMenu, SequenceDisplayWindow.EditMenu, SequenceDisplayWindow.SpeakMenu, SettingsMenu, StructureMenu, WindowsMenu, WindowsMenu.WindowItem

    public interface IMergeItem
extends java.lang.Cloneable
    Provides an interface for a UI component that be included in a hierarchical list. In addition, items can be ordered, grouped and merged (i.e. items from two parents with the same name are combined).

      • MergePosInitial

        static final int MergePosInitial
        The merge position for newly created items. This distinguishes items that have never been positioned from those set to e.g. 0.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MergePosInvalid

        static final int MergePosInvalid
        Indicates an invalid merge position. If a MergeMenu's subItemIndex is set to this value, it will NOT modify the mergePositions of child items added to it.
